My debut track, â€œNumberâ€, outlines heartbreak, betrayal and how hard it is to trust after being stabbed in the back. It accurately represents everything I was feeling at the time of my first big break up. https://t.co/0sJsStQ4jm

This year has been the best and itâ€™s just begun. Iâ€™ve met my heroes, received unique opportunities and made music that Iâ€™m proud of!

Iâ€™d like to thank the team at @soundxyz_ for giving me this chance. Iâ€™m amazed at their work to shift the landscape and give artists a new option.

My aspirations for the future are to learn and grow as an artist. I love soaking up information, taking on new perspectives and meeting new people within the space. I value being a good learner over everything because listening to others leads to more clarity and understanding. https://t.co/kLhAgaJAIV

Last year I took the dive into the world of crypto, NFTs and smart contacts. I quickly learned that there is a lot to web3. But as time went on, I became involved with communities like @soundxyz_ and @dreamsnevrdie and I started to feel like I had a place in the web3 ecosystem. https://t.co/Kbvjf94VTt

Uncertainty has defined every stage of my journey as a young musician. My music never fell into a consistent category for the longest time, leaving me feeling lost and unstable. I bounced between EDM, Pop and Hip Hop for years until I found the SLOE JACK sound.

Iâ€™ve been writing music seriously for about 4 years, but my experiences with production go way back. Bass producers like Skrillex and Flux Pavilion were the reasons I first installed a DAW. I remember being curious as to how their songs were made without any physical instruments. https://t.co/UjfpDSAMBs
